      "raw_text": "SALEM, Ore, April 21.--After\nnumerous complaints from the\npeople Of. Goble and other points\nalong the Northern Pacific between\nPortland and that point regarding\nalleged excessive freight charges,\nthe railroad commission, upon its\nown motion, took up the matter OF\nfreight rates and announced a new\nschedule to replace the one estab\nlished January by the railroad\ncompany.\n\n\nThe Northern Pacific placed in\nforce rates much higher than those\non the books many years. This is\nthe first attempt OF the commission\nIto work out an entire schedule\nthough express rates are now be-\ning worked out."
    }
